txt.en: You have distributed fresh supplies among the Gabil'akkâ.\n\nHlóthi awaits news in Zarkul-sulûn.

'We've received a fresh shipment of supplies that requires distribution among our battalions.\n\n'Deposit these in the supply crates in the trenches and on the boat docked at the lakeshore, as well as the crates in Shakal-atrâd and Ifbar-athrâkh.'
DNT - As TBD requested, you have delivered fresh supplies to the Gabil'akkâ, assisting them in keeping the pressure on their foes.
'You've assisted us in keeping the pressure on our foes, and for that, the Gabil'akkâ thanks you.'
Delivering fresh supplies to the scattered Gabil'akkâ battalions is paramount to the war effort.
March on Gundabad: Resupplying the Forces

There are empty supply crates in Shakal-atrâd, Ifbar-athrâkh, the trenches, and on the docked boat. You should deliver the supplies and replenish the crates.\n\nShakal-atrâd lies to the north-east of Zarkul-sulûn, and Ifbar-athrâkh is close to the forward-most dwarf trench. The dwarf-trenches can be found along the main road towards Gundabad, and the boat near the lake's south-eastern shore.
